{
  "title": "ReFi Roundup #37: Thallo Two-Way Carbon Bridge, Supermodularity âš¡ï¸ğŸ”Œ  & Investing in Climate",
  "slug": "refi-roundup-37",
  "html": "<p>Hey y'all! It's <a href=\"https://twitter.com/shacqeal\">Rudy Fraser</a> of <a href=\"https://www.papertree.earth/\">Papertree.earth</a> back again for another ReFi Roundup! Â If we haven't met â€“ I'm an NYC-based technologist &amp; founder, mutual aid organizer with <a href=\"https://twitter.com/pactDAO\">PactDAO</a>, food sovereignty advocate, and #1 fan of ReFi's 3rd Pillar (Social Justice). Once again I'm grateful to be able to share some of latest topics and conversations at the intersection of regeneration and web3 - let's get right to it!</p><hr><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2022/10/image-21.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1896\" height=\"1078\" srcset=\"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w600/2022/10/image-21.png 600w, __GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w1000/2022/10/image-21.png 1000w, __GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w1600/2022/10/image-21.png 1600w, __GHOST_URL__/content/images/2022/10/image-21.png 1896w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><h2 id=\"thallo-announces-first-two-way-bridge-with-biocarbon-registry\">Thallo announces first two-way bridge with Biocarbon Registry</h2><p>After many months with no substantial incoming supply of environmental assets on-chain, Thallo announced the first two-way bridge with an award-winning Columbian registry called <a href=\"https://t.co/JDdSJ41Ogm\">BioCarbon Registry</a> that specializes in high-quality nature based projects.</p><p>Unlike the first iteration of a carbon bridge pioneered by Toucan, this allows carbon credits to flow on-chain <em>and</em> off-chainâ€”creating a more efficient market. This provides a critical blueprint for the likes of Verra and Gold Standard to consider as they explore their solutions for tokenizing carbon credits. </p><p>Thallo wisely highlighted the project where the credits will initially be sourcedâ€”a REDD+ initiative in the Â ChocÃ³ on the Pacific Coast of Columbia.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/D8CpA1deunQ?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen title=\"Proyecto REDD + Delfines Cupica - BahÃ­a Solano, ChocÃ³ (InglÃ©s)\"></iframe></figure><p>Thallo Founder also highlighted their unique approach to liquidity called \"Dynamic Pooling\"â€”which is a buyer-led filtering process that also \"provides comfort to the Project Developers , who work incredibly hard to provide quality credits.\" </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">We utilise a breakthrough technological innovation that we&#39;ve labelled &quot;Dynamic Pooling&quot; - at its core a buyer-led filtering process. This provides much more comfort to B2B buyers that they are buying quality, transparent credits...</p>&mdash; regenfi.eth (@RyanGled) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/RyanGled/status/1580471465614671873?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 13, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><div class=\"kg-card kg-button-card kg-align-center\"><a href=\"https://www.thallo.io/thallo-biocarbon-registry-launch-worlds-first-two-way-carbon-bridge/\" class=\"kg-btn kg-btn-accent\">Read more</a></div><hr><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2022/10/Fd__adhUAAcEd0o.jpeg\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"792\" srcset=\"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w600/2022/10/Fd__adhUAAcEd0o.jpeg 600w, __GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w1000/2022/10/Fd__adhUAAcEd0o.jpeg 1000w, __GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w1600/2022/10/Fd__adhUAAcEd0o.jpeg 1600w, __GHOST_URL__/content/images/size/w2400/2022/10/Fd__adhUAAcEd0o.jpeg 2400w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"><figcaption>Owocki's graphic depicting supermodularity-</figcaption></figure><h2 id=\"owocki-announces-launch-of-a-regen-venture-studiosupermodular-%E2%9A%A1%EF%B8%8F%F0%9F%94%8C\">Owocki Announces Launch of a Regen Venture Studio - Supermodular âš¡ï¸ğŸ”Œ</h2><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/owocki\">Owocki</a> announced in a recent tweet the launch of a new venture studio with the goal of building a more regenerative digital frontier. It's the next evolution of what was previously called \"Gitcoin Holdings\" which helped launch projects like <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gitcoin\">Gitcoin</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KERNEL0x\">Kernel</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/buidlbox\">Buidlbox</a> (formerly Gitcoin Hackathons), and <a href=\"https://greenpill.party/\">The Green Pill Podcast</a>. It's great to see Owocki transitioning out of leadership at GitcoinDAO into a build-focused role that will undoubtedly unlock innovation throughout the ecosystem.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">i am pleased to announce the launch of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/supermodularxyz?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@supermodularxyz</a><br><br>we are a venture studio that builds regen web3 projects, often on top of &amp; adjacent to <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gitcoin?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@gitcoin</a> &#39;s protocols (QF/grants/passport).<a href=\"https://t.co/7SYdi09s7d\">https://t.co/7SYdi09s7d</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/9yZKtiIM1K\">pic.twitter.com/9yZKtiIM1K</a></p>&mdash; Îwoki (ğŸ¤–,ğŸ’š) (@owocki) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/owocki/status/1579508166613946368?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 10, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><p>You can check out their homepage and roadmap of projects over at <a href=\"https://supermodular.xyz/\">https://supermodular.xyz/</a>. I took a peak at the projects and spied one of my favorite ideas in ReFi right now: HyperCertificates!</p><h3 id=\"hypercerts-pilot-launch-%F0%9F%92%A5\">Hypercerts Pilot Launch ğŸ’¥</h3><p><a href=\"https://hypercerts.xyz/\">Hypercerts</a> are a new tool for building scalable retrospective reward systems, <em>generalized for any impact vector</em>! </p><p>Many ReFi projects build on carbon credits and the voluntary carbon markets. But as David Rodriguez points out in the latest episode of the ReFi Podcast, climate is but 1 of the <a href=\"https://sdgs.un.org/goals\">17 Sustainable Development Goals</a> laid out by the UN and carbon credits themselves have limited impact on Goal 13 (Climate Action). To address <em>all</em> of the challenges facing humanity, we need a more flexible building block. Hypercerts open up the world of ReFi to projects creating other kinds of impact such as in healthcare, education, and even food justice (ğŸ˜‰). Hypercerts could create a transparent parallel market to the not-so-transparent $41T environmental, social, and governance (ESG) market!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2022/10/hypercert_example.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"375\" height=\"561\"><figcaption>Hypercert example from https://hypercerts.xyz/ documentation</figcaption></figure><p>Inline with Owocki's concept of supermodularity, Hypercerts also act as this scalable, <em>interoperable</em> funding layer for public goods. I'm very excited to see how Hypercerts connect different corners of the ReFi world, expand ReFi's scope of impact, and create new opportunities for regeneration ğŸŒ±.</p><h3 id=\"final-thoughts-on-hypercerts\">Final Thoughts on Hypercerts</h3><p>I was so inspired by the team at Protocol Labs and all the research they've done in this space I even started doing <a href=\"https://etherscan.io/address/0x16E3718701EEe950615720cb37F9dD34B1E36035#code%23F2%23L1\">my own experiments with Hypercerts</a>! Papertree rewards funders with our own flavor of Hypercerts as a way to reciprocate the support they've given in helping us fight food insecurity. Each <a href=\"https://opensea.io/collection/hypercerts\">Papertree Hypercert</a> represents 1 months worth of food &amp; groceries provided to a local community and its metadata contains all of the transactions and receipts of the groceries purchased, who it went to, as well as the impact period (for future evaluators)!</p><p>I'm looking forward to continued conversations around Hypercerts and seeing this tool and market evolve. If this stuff excites you too, definitely check out the official <a href=\"https://hypercerts.xyz/\">Hypercerts website</a> and <a href=\"https://t.me/+YF9AYb6zCv1mNDJi\">telegram channel</a>!<br></p><hr><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/OqDIU0czAEQ?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen title=\"ReFi Podcast S2E11: Investing in Climate and Impact Fintech with David Rodriguez from Draft Ventures\"></iframe></figure><h2 id=\"refi-podcast-explores-investing-climate-and-impact-fintech\">ReFi Podcast Explores Investing &amp; Climate and Impact FinTech </h2><p>Formed in 2015, <a href=\"https://draftvc.com/\">Draft Ventures</a> is a firm operating an institutional and direct investment fund, with a fresh focus on early stage (pre-seed, seed rounds) funding for companies in the web3 and climate-solutions spaces. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/davidjrodriguez\">David Rodriguez</a> and co-founder Artia were inspired by the emerging paradigm of regenerative finance (ReFi) and are seeking to underwrite two major trends they're seeing:<br><br>â€ƒâ€ƒ1. The ecology of our planet is in peril and trillions of dollars will be invested <br>â€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒto address that over the next decade.<br>â€ƒâ€ƒ2. An inflection point is occurring for technologies that are disrupting <br>â€ƒâ€ƒâ€ƒfinancial systems and removing middlemen.</p><p>Read Phaedrus's <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/draft-ventures\">deep dive</a>, listen on <a href=\"https://pod.fo/e/14654c\">your favorite podcasting platform</a>, or check out the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/OqDIU0czAEQ\">episode on Youtube</a>.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-button-card kg-align-center\"><a href=\"https://pod.fo/e/14654c\" class=\"kg-btn kg-btn-accent\">Listen to the episode</a></div><div class=\"kg-card kg-header-card kg-width-full kg-size-small kg-style-dark\" style=\"\" data-kg-background-image=\"\"><h2 class=\"kg-header-card-header\" id=\"refi-%F0%9F%90%A6\">ReFi ğŸ¦</h2><h3 class=\"kg-header-card-subheader\" id=\"the-latest-across-refi-twitter-and-beyond\">The latest across ReFi Twitter and beyond...</h3></div><h3 id=\"new-founders-circle-cohort-starting-soon-%F0%9F%8E%89\">New Founder's Circle Cohort Starting Soon! ğŸ‰</h3><p>The ReFi Summer cohort of Founder Circles raised over <strong>$420k</strong> and on <strong>average 3x more</strong> than average grantees during Gitcoin's GR15! Applications open today for the next cohort!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">We&#39;re going to run another cohort of Founder&#39;s Circles leading up to <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/GR16?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#GR16</a> across <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/climate?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#climate</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/DEI?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#DEI</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/DeSci?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#DeSci</a> rounds.<br><br>- Applications open Oct 14<br>- Circles start Nov 1<br>- Circles end Dec 15<br><br>If you&#39;re a founder looking to use <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/web3?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#web3</a> to regenerate people &amp; planetâ€”this is for you!<br><br>5/</p>&mdash; ReFi DAO (@ReFiDAOist) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ReFiDAOist/status/1579874070627090436?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 11, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><div class=\"kg-card kg-button-card kg-align-center\"><a href=\"https://www.notion.so/ReFi-DAO-Founders-Circles-Cohort-02-02e0b226b96f486eb3811e4e58e54d70\" class=\"kg-btn kg-btn-accent\">Learn more</a></div><hr><h3 id=\"offchainlabs-acquires-prysmatic-labs-%F0%9F%A4%9D\">OffchainLabs acquires Prysmatic Labs! ğŸ¤</h3><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/OffchainLabs\">OffchainLabs</a> (the team behind the layer 2 solution <a href=\"https://arbitrum.io/\">Arbitrum</a>) has acquired <a href=\"https://twitter.com/prylabs\">Prysmatic Labs</a> which is the team behind Ethereum's leading consensus client!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Weâ€™re extremely happy to announce that we (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/OffchainLabs?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@OffchainLabs</a>) are acquiring <a href=\"https://twitter.com/prylabs?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@prylabs</a>, the team behind Ethereum&#39;s leading consensus client!<br><br>Letâ€™s dive into details!ğŸ§µğŸ‘‡<a href=\"https://t.co/qIp5JqvZRi\">https://t.co/qIp5JqvZRi</a></p>&mdash; Arbitrum (@arbitrum) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/arbitrum/status/1580190809701613568?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 12, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><hr><h2></h2><p></p><p></p><h3 id=\"thallo-announces-partnership-with-spirals-%F0%9F%8C%80\">Thallo announces partnership with Spirals ğŸŒ€</h3><p>Thallo has announced that they'll be staking their Climate Collective grant with Spirals which is a ReFi protocol seeking to make regeneration the default for the world!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Eager for tangible examples of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/ReFi?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#ReFi</a> (regenerative finance) in action? Check out our partnership with <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SpiralsProtocol?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@SpiralsProtocol</a> ğŸ‘‡<br><br>We&#39;re staking our <a href=\"https://twitter.com/clim8collective?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@clim8collective</a> grant so it passively helps fund high-quality <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/climate?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#climate</a> projects. WIN-WIN-WIN.<a href=\"https://t.co/hLAIisB8vH\">https://t.co/hLAIisB8vH</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/zwz0zqKq9t\">pic.twitter.com/zwz0zqKq9t</a></p>&mdash; Thallo (@thallo_io) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/thallo_io/status/1579842030972579841?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 11, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><hr><h3 id=\"recognizing-indigenous-peoples-day-%F0%9F%8C%BF\">Recognizing Indigenous Peoples Day ğŸŒ¿</h3><p>This week was Indigenous Peoples Day in the U.S. and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/cult_leader_en\">Madam Cult Leader</a> took a moment to write a note reminding us that we owe a lot of our web3 governance elements and coordination principles from indigenous groups and their knowledge.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">On indigenous peoples day, I want people to remember that a lot of the governance â€œinnovationsâ€ in web3 come from indigenous groups in America (NA + SA). <br><br>I suggest everyone read â€œBraiding Sweetgrassâ€ by Robin Wall Kimmerer and follow <a href=\"https://twitter.com/IndigenousWeb3?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@IndigenousWeb3</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/WiisagiMaiingan?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@WiisagiMaiingan</a>.</p>&mdash; madamcultleader.eth/.sol (âš¡ï¸, ğŸ°)(ğŸƒ,ğŸƒ) (@cult_leader_en) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/cult_leader_en/status/1579466826915905538?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 10, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><hr><h3 id=\"upside-down-capitalism-with-skywoman-%F0%9F%AB%B6%F0%9F%8F%BE\">\"Upside Down Capitalism\" with Skywoman ğŸ«¶ğŸ¾</h3><p>While they wouldn't describe themselves as a DAO, Chris Newman and the <a href=\"https://www.skywoman.community/\">Skywoman community</a> are quietly developing their own <a href=\"https://twitter.com/lanitrock/status/1560382722731782144?s=20&amp;t=IzJFLenWECunhwsDVbd61w\">micro niche mycelial networks</a> of farmers, technologists, and entrepreneurs all cooperating to build a better, more equitable food system. Chris recently did a writeup about how they're developing a farm-to-community mutual aid system to promote prosperity rather than address crises (as mutual aid is typically done).</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Design elements of a farm-to-community mutual aid program: insights from dozens of our contributors.<a href=\"https://t.co/PPciWQcfYy\">https://t.co/PPciWQcfYy</a></p>&mdash; SOMETHING ELSE. (@SylvanaquaFarms) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SylvanaquaFarms/status/1576982359123308544?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 3, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><div class=\"kg-card kg-header-card kg-width-full kg-size-small kg-style-dark\" style=\"\" data-kg-background-image=\"\"><h2 class=\"kg-header-card-header\" id=\"refi-events-strong%F0%9F%AA%A9strong\">ReFi Events <strong>ğŸª©</strong></h2><h3 class=\"kg-header-card-subheader\" id=\"get-your-refi-on-with-friends-in-person-and-onlinenbsp\">Get your ReFi on with friends in-person and online...&nbsp;</h3><a href=\"https://refispring.com/\" class=\"kg-header-card-button\">View more</a></div><h2 id=\"looking-forward-%F0%9F%93%8D\">Looking Forward ğŸ“</h2><p><em>Some of the exciting events coming up soon... Make sure to grab some tickets and support the ReFi regenerative renaissance wherever you are from! </em></p><h3 id=\"blockchain-social-impact-summit\">Blockchain &amp; Social Impact Summit</h3><p>Insightful sessions and meaningful connections aligned on the purpose of making a difference for a better world!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card kg-card-hascaption\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Our Blockchain and Social Impact in Abuja is coming soon, on October 29th.<br>Get inspired by some of the biggest names in the crypto and tech ecosystem in Nigeria across various topics related to blockchain, and get to know more about impactful solutions and projects.<br><br>(1/2) <a href=\"https://t.co/VENLhuDftd\">pic.twitter.com/VENLhuDftd</a></p>&mdash; impactMarket | $PACT (@impactMarket_) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/impactMarket_/status/1580230448441352193?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 12, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n<figcaption>\\</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"sovereign-nature-initiative-monthly-talk\">Sovereign Nature Initiative Monthly Talk</h3><p>Attend SNI's monthly talk with Caroline Ng'weno, a Nairobi-based wildlife ecologist who will be discussing solutions for coexisting with wildlife!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Register below to attend our monthly talk happening next Thursday, October 20, from 5-6pm CET!<br><br>This will be a conversation you won&#39;t want to miss! <a href=\"https://t.co/NOWWnb1TLd\">https://t.co/NOWWnb1TLd</a></p>&mdash; Sovereign Nature Initiative (@sovereignnature) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/sovereignnature/status/1580102981227536384?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 12, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><h3 id=\"ipfs-camp-2022\">IPFS Camp 2022</h3><p>Join the entire IPFS community including devs, operators, implementers, and researchers for talks, hackathons, and more in Lisbon.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">ğŸ‘€ A sneak peek of our lineup at <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/IPFSCamp?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#IPFSCamp</a>.<br><br>ğŸ« Grab those tickets: <a href=\"https://t.co/JupaREM6pM\">https://t.co/JupaREM6pM</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/1kzhVG9MAA\">pic.twitter.com/1kzhVG9MAA</a></p>&mdash; IPFS (@IPFS) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/IPFS/status/1580202639526019072?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 12, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><h3 id=\"ideas-2022-by-coindesk\">I.D.E.A.S. 2022 by CoinDesk</h3><p>CoinDesk's \"Investing in Digital Enterprises and Assets\" Summit will be in NYC October 18-19, 2022 and seeks to connect the digital economy with traditional finance. Awesome to see Sid Jha featured below!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">â€œA lot of the climate data sits in very archaic servers for government agencies, academic agencies, other nonprofits, and often can be overwritten,â€ <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SidJhaCEO?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@SidJhaCEO</a> says for <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/CoinDeskIDEAS?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#CoinDeskIDEAS</a> Week.<a href=\"https://t.co/faT8qBCWF3\">https://t.co/faT8qBCWF3</a></p>&mdash; CoinDesk (@CoinDesk) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CoinDesk/status/1580655575892774913?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 13, 2022</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n</figure><h3 id=\"socap-22\">SOCAP 22</h3><p>Impact investingâ€™s biggest event brings together a diverse roster of impact leaders in San Francisc